        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 3:13PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 313 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Linden, or 14 miles west of Atlanta, moving northeast
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texarkana, Atlanta, Wake Village, Nash, Hooks, Linden, Queen City,
Redwater, Maud, Red Lick, Leary, Douglassville, Marietta, Domino,
Red Hill, Bryans Mill and Pleasant Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
